# Copy to .env.local and fill in from your Supabase project:
#   Supabase dashboard → Connect → Project URL + Publishable key
#
# The key is labelled "Publishable" (sb_publishable_...) on newer projects and
# "anon public" on older ones — same key, either works here.
#
# Both values are PUBLIC — they ship inside the client bundle, and that's fine:
# row-level security is what protects the data, not the secrecy of these keys.
# Never put the secret key (sb_secret_... / service_role) in a VITE_ variable;
# anything VITE_-prefixed is readable by every visitor.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_your-key-here

# Founder-side product analytics (PostHog) — optional. Get from posthog.com →
# Project settings → Project API Key. Never shown to users; see src/lib/analytics.js.
# Leave unset and analytics silently no-op, same guest-degradation pattern as Supabase.
VITE_POSTHOG_PROJECT_TOKEN=phc_your-project-token-here
VITE_POSTHOG_HOST=https://eu.i.posthog.com
